HEADWORD: Luciferin
<hw>Lu*cif"er*in</hw> <pr>(l⟦oomac⟧*s⟦icr⟧f"⟦etil⟧r*⟦icr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biochem.)</fld> <def>any of several substances found
in luminescent organisms (such as the firefly, <spn>Photinus
pyralis</spn>) which, when oxidized, produces an almost heatless light.
It was first isolated from fireflies, and is the source of the firefly
luminescence. See also <styp><er>firefly luciferin</er></styp></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luciferase</ent>⟦br⟧
